      <title>Hot in Herre - GovTrack.us</title>
      <link>https://www.govtrack.us/posts/424/2024-06-17_hot-in-herre</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.govtrack.us/posts/424/2024-06-17_hot-in-herre</guid>
      <description>&lt;div id="content"&gt; 				 			   	  				 &lt;h1&gt;Hot in Herre&lt;/h1&gt;  &lt;div class="row"&gt;     &lt;div class="col-md order-md-2" style="margin-bottom: 2em"&gt;         &lt;div class="ms-md-3" style="border: 1px solid #777; border-radius: 1em; padding: 1em; background-color: #F9F9F9;"&gt;         &lt;h2&gt;Get Legislative Preview Updates In Your Inbox!&lt;/h2&gt;         &lt;p&gt;Sign up (it&amp;rsquo;s free!) to get posts like this straight to your inbox. You&amp;rsquo;ll be able to choose posts from these categories:&lt;/p&gt;         &lt;p&gt;Legislative Recap &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; Legislative Preview &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; Analysis and Commentary &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; News About GovTrack &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; Using GovTrack Tips&lt;/p&gt;         &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/accounts/lists" class="btn btn-primary"&gt;Sign Up &amp;raquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;      &lt;div class="col-md"&gt;        &lt;p&gt;           Jun 17, 2024           &amp;middot; by Daniel Schuman       &lt;/p&gt;        &lt;p&gt;Hello Trackers!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The House of Representatives&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;a href="https://www.majorityleader.gov/uploadedfiles/2024_house_calendar_-_one_page_-_revised_april_2024.pdf"&gt;in recess&lt;/a&gt; this week and &lt;strong&gt;the Senate&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.democrats.senate.gov/2024/06/13/schedule-for-monday-june-17-2024"&gt;reconvenes on Monday&lt;/a&gt; to consider judicial nominations over the course of the week.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Senate&lt;/strong&gt; has &lt;a href="https://www.congress.gov/committee-schedule/weekly/2024/06/17"&gt;11 committee proceedings&lt;/a&gt; scheduled for this week, including two before the Appropriations Committee and two before the Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs Committee. The Commerce and Judiciary committees both have &lt;a href="https://www.senate.gov/about/research-tools/glossary.htm#M"&gt;markups&lt;/a&gt; scheduled, which is when they consider legislation.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Compared to last week’s very busy schedule, it will be quiet on Capitol Hill. One way that I can tell is the number of automatic responses from emails sent to Capitol Hill — “Thank you for emailing. I will be out of the office until ….” — went up significantly on Friday.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;We did receive some mail last week asking what “red meat” legislation is. According to Taegan Goddard’s &lt;a href="https://politicaldictionary.com/words/red-meat/"&gt;political dictionary&lt;/a&gt;, red meat is “a term used in politics to refer to statements or policies that are designed to appeal to a political party’s base or to generate a strong emotional response from voters. These statements or policies often involve controversial or divisive issues, such as immigration or gun control, and are meant to stir up strong feelings among supporters.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It’s &lt;a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/weather/interactive/2023/heat-waves-map-us-tracker/?itid=hp-more-top-stories_p004_f011"&gt;going to be very hot&lt;/a&gt;, so take it easy out there.&lt;/p&gt;      &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;  &lt;hr&gt;  &lt;p&gt;    Let us know what you think about these updates    by tooting us on &lt;a rel="me" href="https://mastodon.social/@GovTrack" title="Mastodon"&gt;&lt;i class="fab fa-mastodon"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Mastodon&lt;/a&gt;    or &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/contact" style="text-decoration: none"&gt;&lt;i class="fas fa-envelope"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; sending us an email&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;    			&lt;/div&gt;</description>
