    <item>
      <title>Grab Bag Week - GovTrack.us</title>
      <link>https://www.govtrack.us/posts/423/2024-06-14_grab-bag-week</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.govtrack.us/posts/423/2024-06-14_grab-bag-week</guid>
      <description>&lt;div id="content"&gt; 				 			   	  				 &lt;h1&gt;Grab Bag Week&lt;/h1&gt;  &lt;div class="row"&gt;     &lt;div class="col-md order-md-2" style="margin-bottom: 2em"&gt;         &lt;div class="ms-md-3" style="border: 1px solid #777; border-radius: 1em; padding: 1em; background-color: #F9F9F9;"&gt;         &lt;h2&gt;Get Legislative Recap Updates In Your Inbox!&lt;/h2&gt;         &lt;p&gt;Sign up (it&amp;rsquo;s free!) to get posts like this straight to your inbox. You&amp;rsquo;ll be able to choose posts from these categories:&lt;/p&gt;         &lt;p&gt;Legislative Recap &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; Legislative Preview &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; Analysis and Commentary &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; News About GovTrack &amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp; Using GovTrack Tips&lt;/p&gt;         &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/accounts/lists" class="btn btn-primary"&gt;Sign Up &amp;raquo;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;      &lt;div class="col-md"&gt;        &lt;p&gt;           Jun 14, 2024           &amp;middot; by Amy West       &lt;/p&gt;        &lt;p&gt;A bit of a busy week in Congress, mostly in the House. There was some partisan action, some very traditional legislating on foreign policy and three bills that will directly affect Americans in different ways.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Garland Contempt Vote&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hres1292"&gt;H.Res. 1292: Recommending that the House of Representatives find United States Attorney General Merrick B. Garland in contempt of Congress for refusal to comply with a subpoena duly issued by the Committee on the Judiciary&lt;/a&gt;. The House had previously demanded, and received, a written transcript of Special Counsel Robert Hur's interview with President Biden regarding the classified documents found in his possession in the last two years. The House Judiciary then demanded the audio recordings which the Department of Justice refused to hand over citing the White House's claim of executive privilege. The &lt;a href="https://apnews.com/article/garland-contempt-congress-vote-biden-classified-documents-20f5e8f48cfd8390eb695d13079ca306"&gt;AP reported the politics of it&lt;/a&gt; in detail. The vote was &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/h260"&gt;216-207&lt;/a&gt; with one Republican voting no.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Diplomacy&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/s138/summary"&gt;S. 138: Promoting a Resolution to the Tibet-China Dispute Act&lt;/a&gt; defines Tibet to include areas currently claimed by China and to expand efforts to counter Chinese government propaganda. It required a 2/3rds majority to pass and it got it with &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/h252"&gt;391-26&lt;/a&gt;. All 26 no votes were cast by Republicans. The bill now goes to the President and will become law soon.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;No Hidden Hotel Fees&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr6543"&gt;H.R. 6543: No Hidden Fees on Extra Expenses for Stays Act of 2023&lt;/a&gt; will require that hotels and similar short-term stay businesses tell prospective customers up front what any additional fees will be beyond the room rates. It needed a 2/3rds majority and got it with &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/h248"&gt;384-25&lt;/a&gt;. All 25 no votes were from Republicans.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Wastewater Pollution&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr2964/summary"&gt;H.R. 2964: Wastewater Infrastructure Pollution Prevention and Environmental Safety Act&lt;/a&gt; requires that the labeling for certain premoistened, nonwoven wipes (e.g., baby wipes, cleaning wipes, or personal care wipes) to clearly and conspicuously say Do Not Flush. This required a 2/3rds majority and got it with &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/h249"&gt;351-56&lt;/a&gt;. All 56 no votes were cast by Republicans.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;National Defense Authorization Act (NDAA)&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/118/hr8070"&gt;H.R. 8070: Servicemember Quality of Life Improvement and National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2025&lt;/a&gt; passed, with amendments, by &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/118-2024/h279"&gt;217-199&lt;/a&gt;. Three Republicans voted no, six Democrats voted yes. A number of controversial amendments narrowly passed as well, but will almost certainly will not appear in whatever final product is presented to the President. These include amendments to&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;prohibit services for gender transition,&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;reimbursement for abortion services,&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;permanent hiring freezes on diversity related positions in the DoD,&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;eliminating any offices focused on diversity,&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;eliminating the position of Chief Diversity Officer,&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;prohibit funding of companies who function to demonetize domestic entities based on their lawful speech (aka &lt;a href="https://amendments-rules.house.gov/amendments/WILLTX_062_xml240607115518651.pdf?_gl=1*gs7cuu*_ga*MTE2ODkxNTY5Mi4xNjk4MTc1Mzk2*_ga_N4RTJ5D08B*MTcxODM5MjMzMy4yLjEuMTcxODM5MzQ0Ni4wLjAuMA.."&gt;prohibit funding of fact checking organizations&lt;/a&gt;),&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;prohibiting DoD from acquiring materials that promote "radical gender ideology" or porn, and&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;prohibit funding for the Countering Extremist Activity Working Group (&lt;a href="https://www.militarytimes.com/flashpoints/extremism-disinformation/2023/12/09/the-pentagon-working-group-to-combat-extremism-could-be-finished/"&gt;background&lt;/a&gt; from Military Times).&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;      &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;  &lt;hr&gt;  &lt;p&gt;    Let us know what you think about these updates    by tooting us on &lt;a rel="me" href="https://mastodon.social/@GovTrack" title="Mastodon"&gt;&lt;i class="fab fa-mastodon"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Mastodon&lt;/a&gt;    or &lt;a href="https://www.govtrack.us/contact" style="text-decoration: none"&gt;&lt;i class="fas fa-envelope"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; sending us an email&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;    			&lt;/div&gt;</description>
